{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, adding the input signal back to the output prevents signal dropout as the network learns to generalize.",
    "Figure 15 extends the example from Fig. 4 to show the residual vector formed from the summation of the original vector \"Machine\" and its attention version \"Machine.a\".",
    "The figure labels the residual vector as \"Machine.r\".",
    "Similarly, the figure shows the residual vector (\"Learning.r\") formed from the summation of the original vector \"Learning\" and its attention version \"Learning.a\".",
    "The effect of forming the residual was to boost the attention vector magnitudes towards the original vectors."
  ]
}